# ARM→PPC JIT Recompiler: Diagnosis & Fixes

## Root Cause Analysis

The crash symptoms tell a clear story:

```
Invalid read from 0x000000e3, PC = 0x800ceaf8   ← reading near-zero address
Invalid read from 0x000000df, PC = 0x800ceb08   ← same pattern
Exception (ISI) occurred!                         ← instruction fetch fault
PC = 0x02000A5c  (ARM address being executed as PPC)
```

The PC landed at `0x02000A5c` — an ARM DS RAM address — meaning the JIT returned to **ARM code as if it were PPC code**. This points to several compounding bugs:

---

## Bug 1: `computeOffsets()` Uses Wrong Hard-Coded Values

This is the **primary bug**. The offsets assume a specific memory layout that almost certainly doesn't match your actual build.

```cpp
// BROKEN: assumes exact padding, ignores vtable, alignment, etc.
off_halted       = 8;
off_registersUsr = 160;
off_cpsr         = 284;
off_cycles       = 312;
```

**Fix:** Use `offsetof()` — but since the fields are private, add a helper:

```cpp
// Add to interpreter.h (public section):
public:
    static size_t offset_registersUsr() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, registersUsr);
    }
    static size_t offset_cpsr() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, cpsr);
    }
    static size_t offset_cycles() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, cycles);
    }
    static size_t offset_halted() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, halted);
    }
    static size_t offset_pcData() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, pcData);
    }
    static size_t offset_pipeline() {
        return offsetof(Interpreter, pipeline);
    }
```

```cpp
// jit_ppc.cpp — fix computeOffsets():
static void computeOffsets() {
    off_halted       = Interpreter::offset_halted();
    off_pcData       = Interpreter::offset_pcData();
    off_pipeline     = Interpreter::offset_pipeline();
    off_registersUsr = Interpreter::offset_registersUsr();
    off_cpsr         = Interpreter::offset_cpsr();
    off_cycles       = Interpreter::offset_cycles();

    // Debug: print so you can verify
    printf("[JIT] Offsets: halted=%zu pcData=%zu pipeline=%zu "
           "registersUsr=%zu cpsr=%zu cycles=%zu\n",
           off_halted, off_pcData, off_pipeline,
           off_registersUsr, off_cpsr, off_cycles);
}
```

