## Bug 3: Stack Frame Overflow

```cpp
static const int FRAME_SIZE    = 128;
static const int FRAME_LR      = 124;   // LR at byte 124
static const int FRAME_R14     = 8;     // r14-r26 = 13 regs × 4 = 52 bytes: [8..59]
static const int FRAME_REGSYNC = 64;    // 17 words × 4 = 68 bytes: [64..131]
```

`FRAME_REGSYNC + 17*4 = 64 + 68 = 132 > 128` — **overflow corrupts the caller's frame**.

Additionally, PPC ABI requires the back-chain word at `[r1+0]` and the caller's LR save area at `[r1+4]`. Your frame layout violates this.

**Fix:**

```cpp
// Corrected frame layout (must be 16-byte aligned on Wii):
// [r1+0]   = back-chain (written by stwu automatically)
// [r1+4]   = (ABI: caller LR save — leave for OS/debugger)
// [r1+8]   = our saved LR
// [r1+12]  = padding
// [r1+16]  = saved r14..r26 (13 regs × 4 = 52 bytes) → [16..67]
// [r1+68]  = padding to align
// [r1+72]  = ARM regs sync area (17 × 4 = 68 bytes)  → [72..139]
// [r1+140] = padding
// Total needed: 140 → round up to 160 (16-byte aligned)

static const int FRAME_SIZE    = 160;
static const int FRAME_LR      = 8;
static const int FRAME_R14     = 16;
static const int FRAME_REGSYNC = 72;
```

Update all uses of these constants in `emit_prologue`, `emit_epilogue`, `emit_syncToInterp`, `emit_syncFromInterp`, and `emit_loadStore`.

