## Bug 7: `emit_loadStore` Saves/Restores Volatile Regs Incorrectly

```cpp
// After the call, you do:
if (isLoad)
    ctx.emit(ppc_stw(3, VSAVE + 0 * 4, 1)); // overwrite slot 0 with result

for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
    ctx.emit(ppc_lwz(3 + i, VSAVE + i * 4, 1));  // ← OVERWRITES r3 with old value!

if (isLoad) {
    if (ppcRd != 3)
        ctx.emit(ppc_mr(ppcRd, 3));  // ← r3 now has OLD value, not result!
}
```

**Fix:**

```cpp
if (isLoad) {
    // Save result before restoring volatiles
    ctx.emit(ppc_mr(PPC_TMP0, 3));  // PPC_TMP0 = r25, non-volatile, safe
}

// Restore volatile ARM regs
for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
    ctx.emit(ppc_lwz(3 + i, VSAVE + i * 4, 1));

if (isLoad) {
    ctx.emit(ppc_mr(ppcRd, PPC_TMP0));  // now set destination from saved result
}
```

