## Summary of All Fixes

| # | Bug | Impact |
|---|-----|--------|
| 1 | Hard-coded wrong struct offsets | **Critical** — reads wrong memory |
| 2 | Sync bypasses register bank indirection | **Critical** — wrong register values in banked modes |
| 3 | Stack frame too small (overflow) | **Critical** — corrupts caller frame |
| 4 | `emit_li32` sign-extends 16-bit values | **Critical** — generates wrong addresses (your `0xe3` crash) |
| 5 | Condition patch mask too narrow | Minor — wrong branch targets |
| 6 | Frame size not 16-byte aligned | ABI violation — intermittent crashes |
| 7 | Load result overwritten by volatile restore | **High** — loads garbage values |
| 8 | R15 loaded from interp then immediately overwritten | Medium — wastes cycles, potential conflict |

Fix these in order — bugs 1, 2, 3, and 4 alone explain all the symptoms in your crash log.
